Continuing education expenses are above-the-line deduction up to $2,500 annually for mandatory CE starting 2025.

knowledge_base.question: Washington State Simple Licensing Requirements
knowledge_base.answer: Washington has among the simplest contractor licensing: No experience requirements, no education requirements, no examination for general contractors. $30,000 surety bond (increased July 2024), $250,000 minimum general liability insurance ($200K public liability + $50K property damage OR $250K combined). Registration fee $141.10 for 2 years. Must register with Secretary of State, obtain UBI number, get EIN. 3-4 week processing for mail applications.

knowledge_base.question: How much does a Georgia contractor license cost?
knowledge_base.answer: Georgia contractor license costs: Application fee is $200. Total costs range from $300-400 including all fees. Additionally, a $10,000 surety bond is required for general contractors. Exam fees are separate. Total investment typically ranges from $2,500-3,500 including preparation and all requirements.

knowledge_base.question: What is the Georgia contractor license application process?
knowledge_base.answer: Georgia contractor license application process: 1) Submit application with $200 fee, 2) Provide proof of 4 years experience or equivalent education, 3) Pass Business & Law exam (110 questions, 4 hours), 4) Pass Trade exam (110 questions, 4 hours), 5) Obtain $10,000 surety bond, 6) Complete background check. Process typically takes 30-45 days.

knowledge_base.question: Georgia license cost

knowledge_base.question: Georgia exam requirements
knowledge_base.answer: Georgia contractor exam requirements: Two exams required - Business & Law exam (110 questions, 4 hours) and Trade exam (110 questions, 4 hours). Both require 70% passing score. Exams cover business practices, law, safety, and trade-specific knowledge.

knowledge_base.question: Georgia bond requirements
knowledge_base.answer: Georgia contractor bond requirements: General contractors must obtain a $10,000 surety bond. The bond protects consumers from contractor default or failure to meet obligations. Bond costs typically 1-3% of bond amount annually ($100-300/year) based on credit score.

knowledge_base.question: Georgia experience requirements
knowledge_base.answer: Georgia contractor experience requirements: 4 years of verifiable experience in the construction industry OR equivalent education (bachelor's degree in construction-related field counts as 2 years, associate's degree counts as 1 year). Experience must be documented with tax records, W-2s, or employer verification.
